{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μετα-στρέφω</b>, <br /> <i>aorist</i> <i>passive</i> -εστρέφθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.258, +others, -εστράφην [ᾰ] 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.121, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>turn about, turn round</b>, τῶ κε Ποσειδάων.. αἶψα μεταστρέψειε νόον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.52; εἴ κεν Ἀχιλλεὺς ἐκ χόλου.. μεταστρέψῃ φίλον ἦτορ 10.107; τὸ πρόσωπον πρός τι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 190e \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: —<i>middle</i>, μεταστρέφεσθαι πρὸς τὸ μαλθακώτερον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 538 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, <b>turn oneself about, turn about</b>, whether to face the enemy, στῆ δὲ μεταστρεφθείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.595, 15.591, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.211 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; or to flee, τῷ δὲ μεταστρεφθέντι μεταφρένῳ ἐν δόρυ πῆξεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.258 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; simply, <b>turn round</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.121, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 116d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>turn about</b> (to see if any one follows), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 125, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.221 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>recur</b>, ἐπὶ τὰ προειρημένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 428d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>turn round, retort</b>, αἰτίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 41.13. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>twist</b> or <b>turn all ways</b>, πάντα μεταστρέφοντα λόγον βασανίζειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 191c; λόγους ἄνω καὶ κάτω μ. [prev. author] “Phdr.” 272b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>turn upside down</b>, ἅπαντα μ. τύχη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 111 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τἄνω κάτω ὁ βίος μεταστραφείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 5. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>misrepresent</b>, [δικαιοσύνης καὶ ἀδικίας] τὴν δύναμιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 367a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>change, alter</b>, τὸ δίκαιον οὐκ ἔστι μεταστρέψαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1376b21, compare 1412a33 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>invert</b>, τὰ τοῦ Ξενοφάνους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 1377a23 \">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ὁρᾷς γὰρ τἄμ᾽ ὅσῳ μετεστράφη how my fortunes <b>are changed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 1329; τὸ ψήφισμ᾽ ὅπως μεταστραφείη 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 537. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> ἀντὶ τοῦ ἰῶτα ἦτα μ. <b>use</b> one <b>for</b> another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 418c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>turn another way, change one's ways</b>, ἦ τι μεταστρέψει; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.203: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> <i>participle</i> μεταστρέψας <b>contrariwise</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 457a (_plural_), “R.” 587d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>turn so as to punish</b> or <b>avenge</b>, of the gods, μή τι μεταστρέψωσιν ἀγασσάμενοι κακὰ ἔργα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.67 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] (unless <i>transitive</i>, <b>turn back</b> (upon the sinners),[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare μετάτροπος 2). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>care for, regard</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1226. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3344","accentedUnicode":"μεταστρέφω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0276","matchingForm":"ἀμετάθετος","stepTransliteration":"ametathetos","gloss":"unchangeable","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不更改","_es_Gloss":"inmutable","_zh_Gloss":"不更改"},{"strongNumber":"G3326","matchingForm":"μετά","stepTransliteration":"meta","gloss":"with/after","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同","_es_Gloss":"con/después","_zh_Gloss":"同"},{"strongNumber":"G3327","matchingForm":"μεταβαίνω","stepTransliteration":"metabainō","gloss":"to depart","_zh_tw_Gloss":"離開","_es_Gloss":"salir","_zh_Gloss":"离开"},{"strongNumber":"G3328","matchingForm":"μεταβάλλω","stepTransliteration":"metaballō","gloss":"to change mind","_zh_tw_Gloss":"就轉念","_es_Gloss":"cambiar de parecer","_zh_Gloss":"就转念"},{"strongNumber":"G3329","matchingForm":"μετάγω","stepTransliteration":"metagō","gloss":"to turn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"能調動, 轉動","_es_Gloss":"girar","_zh_Gloss":"能调动, 转动"},{"strongNumber":"G3331","matchingForm":"μετάθεσις","stepTransliteration":"metathesis","gloss":"removal/change","_zh_tw_Gloss":"接去, 要被挪去","_es_Gloss":"remocion/cambio","_zh_Gloss":"接去, 要被挪去"},{"strongNumber":"G3332","matchingForm":"μεταίρω","stepTransliteration":"metairō","gloss":"to leave","_zh_tw_Gloss":"就離, 就離開","_es_Gloss":"irse","_zh_Gloss":"就离, 就离开"},{"strongNumber":"G3334","matchingForm":"μετακινέω","stepTransliteration":"metakineō","gloss":"to shift","_zh_tw_Gloss":"挪動","_es_Gloss":"moverse","_zh_Gloss":"挪动"},{"strongNumber":"G3335","matchingForm":"μεταλαμβάνω","stepTransliteration":"metalambanō","gloss":"to partake","_